# Context

Test 5 (diagnostics/test5_failure_window_inspection.py) dumped the full 30×10 input window for the worst-error sample of MLP and GRU as CSVs. The failure at idx 38180 has torDes = 0, torAct = +106 Nm, i < 0. This is a post-release ringing event — the controller has commanded zero but the HEJ-90's spring hasn't discharged.

Before trying longer windows or new features, confirm what the existing 30-sample window actually contains at the moment of failure. Specifically: does torEst carry the 106 Nm state, or has it already collapsed to follow the command?

If torEst has collapsed, then the model has no state information at all and longer windows may not help. If torEst still carries momentum, then 30 ms is simply too short to resolve the decay and longer windows are the right fix.

